    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-12-19T21:06:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-12-19T21:06:00-05:00" n="261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <head>261. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d261fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 303/12–1860. Confidential; Priority. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_HVF1">Hartley</persName>, initialed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_CWI1">Cargo</persName>, cleared with <gloss target="#t_FE1"
                            >FE</gloss> and in substance with <persName corresp="#p_MGN1"
                            >Monsma</persName>, and approved by <persName corresp="#p_SJJ1"
                            >Sisco</persName> who signed for Herter.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1960-12-19T21:06:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1960—9:06 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1188. Re Mauritanian Membership.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>USGADel should endeavor persuade sponsors 11-power draft<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d261fn2">Reference is to a draft resolution favoring
                            Mauritania’s admission to the United Nations, submitted to the <gloss
                                target="#t_UN1">U.N</gloss>. General Assembly by 11 African nations.
                            Its text was transmitted to the Department in telegram 1807 from <gloss
                                target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, December 18. (<hi rend="italic"
                                >Ibid</hi>.) For text, see U.N. doc. <gloss target="#t_A1"
                                >A</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss>.335.</note> agree
                        postpone consideration their resolution until resumed session on grounds
                        Soviet amendments raise highly controversial Outer Mongolian issue and
                        consideration this issue now could result in either postponement recess date
                        or failure complete more pressing questions prior recess. If unsuccessful
                        this effort, USGADel should support 11-power draft resolution reported
                            <gloss target="#t_URTEL1">urtel</gloss> 1807.</item>
                    <pb facs="0492" n="462" xml:id="pg_462"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>As proposed <gloss target="#t_REFTEL1">reftel</gloss> USGADel should
                        strongly oppose any amendment to include Outer Mongolia this draft
                        resolution and also oppose consideration as separate resolution Outer
                        Mongolia and other pending applications at this time. <gloss
                            target="#t_DEL1">Del</gloss> should actively seek support other friendly
                            <gloss target="#t_DEL1">del</gloss>s for this purpose.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>If draft resolution amended to include Outer Mongolia, delegation should
                        abstain on amended resolution.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>USGADel should endeavor persuade sponsors 11-power draft substitute
                        “finding” for “decision” in operative paragraph 2 draft resolution since
                            <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> cannot make decisions.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>USGADel should make no statements or explanations of vote.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">Herter</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
